## 📄 Week 2 Summary (Data Structures & Functions)
In Week 2, I learned about Python data structures and functions, which are essential for organizing and processing data efficiently. I studied lists, tuples, dictionaries, and sets, and understood how each structure is used in different situations. These helped me store and manipulate data in a structured way.
I also learned how to create and use functions to make code reusable and modular. Concepts like lambda functions and list comprehension helped me write shorter and more efficient code. Additionally, I gained a basic understanding of recursion.
Through hands-on practice, I worked on tasks such as finding the sum of squares and filtering specific values from a dataset. These exercises improved my logical thinking and coding skills.
As part of the client project, I developed a data cleaning script that removed duplicate values and filtered unnecessary data. This gave me practical experience in preparing raw data for analysis.
Overall, this week enhanced my understanding of data handling and improved my ability to write efficient and structured Python programs.
